===Alternative forms===
* {{l|el|Ελλάς|tr=Ellás|g=f}}

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|grc|el}} {{term|Ἑλλάδα||tr=Hellada|lang=grc}}, accusative form of {{term|Ἑλλάς||Greece|tr=Hellas|lang=grc}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/eˈlaða/|lang=el}}

===Proper noun===
{{el-noun-proper|f|Elláda}}
# [[Greece]]

====Usage notes====
{{l|el|Ελλάς}} is the former, [[Katharevousa]], word for what in Standard Modern Greek is now called {{l|el|Ελλάδα}}. Greece is formally referred to as the {{l|el|[[ελληνικός|Ελληνική]] [[δημοκρατία|Δημοκρατία]]|gloss=the Hellenic Republic}}.

